The Oyo State Football Association (OYSFA) has announced that draws for the 2023 edition of the Oyo State Federation Cup will take place today, Monday, at the Lekan Salami Sports Complex, Adamasingba, Ibadan. 20 clubs will participate in the competition this year. The top two teams in the competition will represent the state in the national Federation Cup. Saki United were crowned champions last year after beating Oyo State Housing Corporation in the final. Shooting Stars and Crown Football Club of Ogbomosho, the top two sides in the state, are the frontrunners to win the title this year. The national Federation Cup will kick-off in May.